text: :For the brachiopod genus, see Limbella (brachiopod). Limbella is a genus of mosses in the family Amblystegiaceae. It contains the following species (but this list may be incomplete): * Limbella fryei, (R.S. Williams) Ochyra. * Limbella tricostata, (Sull.) Müll. Hal. ex E.B. Bartram * Limbella bartlettii * Limbella conspissata * Limbella limbata ==References== Category:Hypnales Category:Moss genera Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
title: Limbella
